Here are both approaches in .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

**1. Passing a simple string (product ID):**

```csharp
// From ProductListPage or its ViewModel
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"ProductDetailsPage?productId={product.Id}");
```

**2. Passing a complex object:**

```csharp
var parameters = new Dictionary<string, object>
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }  // full Product object
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("ProductDetailsPage", parameters);
```

**Receiving both via `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            string productId = idObj.ToString();
            // fetch product from service, etc.
            LoadProduct(productId);
        }

        // Approach 2: full object (passed via dictionary overload)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var productObj) 
            && productObj is Product product)
        {
            Name = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
            // use directly — no deserialization needed
        }
    }
}
```

**Wire up the ViewModel as `BindingContext`:**

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Register the route and DI:**

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs / AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("ProductDetailsPage", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// MauiProgram.cs
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| **Method** | URI query string | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| **Type in `ApplyQueryAttributes`** | arrives as `string` | arrives as the original object type |
| **Best for** | IDs, simple values, deep links | Rich objects already in memory |

> **Tip:** Shell calls `ApplyQueryAttributes` on the `BindingContext` automatically if it implements `IQueryAttributable` — no manual plumbing needed beyond setting the `BindingContext`.
